I've done several studies that involve categorizing like this, and I found this to be one of the hardest ones. It was hard for me to look quickly at a word and know if it was abstract or concrete. I've always found that I can classify pictures much faster than words in this type of study--my brain seems to process and categorize pictures faster, but kind of stall when processing words (I can read them quickly, but it takes longer to categorize them).

To be honest, some of the categorization didn't really make sense to me/ Global is "bigger" but I don't think of it as any more "abstract" than local (actually local seems much more vague to me as there can be varying sizes of local, but global is only one thing). And why is automatic abstract? It seems like the opposite of abstract to me.
